## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="518a1-102">Ten obiekt jest podobny do `tag` elementu zdefiniowanego przez organizacja World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) [Specyfikacja gramatyki rozpoznawania mowy (SRGS) w wersji 1,0.](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201761).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-102">This object is similar to the `tag` element defined by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) [Speech Recognition Grammar Specification (SRGS) Version 1.0.](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201761).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="518a1-103"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag.Value%2A> Jednak właściwość tego obiektu nie może być skryptem.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-103">However, the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag.Value%2A> property of this object cannot be script.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="518a1-104"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag.Value%2A> Zawartość może być typu <xref:System.Boolean>, <xref:System.Double>, <xref:System.Int32>, lub <xref:System.String>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-104">The contents of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag.Value%2A> can be of the type <xref:System.Boolean>, <xref:System.Double>, <xref:System.Int32>, or <xref:System.String>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="518a1-105">Wartości ciągu muszą być ujęte w cudzysłów.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-105">String values must be enclosed in double quotes.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="518a1-106">Aby dodać semantykę jako skrypt, użyj <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-106">To add semantics as script, use <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="518a1-107">Poniższy przykład tworzy gramatykę do wybierania miast dla lotu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-107">The following example creates a grammar for choosing the cities for a flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="518a1-108">W przykładzie zastosowano <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag.%23ctor%2A> przypisanie wartości semantycznej do każdego miasta, czyli kodu dla lotniska miasta.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-108">The example uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag.%23ctor%2A> to assign a semantic value to each city, which is the code for the city's airport.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="518a1-109">Przykład tworzy dwa <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> wystąpienia, z których każdy określa klucz semantyczny.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-109">The example constructs two <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> instances, each of which specifies a semantic key.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="518a1-110">Obie reguły odwołują się do <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> tego samego obiektu `cities`, o nazwie, ale Tagi wynik rozpoznawania z odwołania reguły z innym kluczem semantycznym.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-110">Both rule references target the same <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object, named `cities`, but tag the recognition result from the rule reference with a different semantic key.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="518a1-111">Klucz semantyczny identyfikuje uznawany miasto jako miasto wysyłki lub miasto przybycia dla lotu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-111">The semantic key identifies a recognized city as the departure city or the arrival city for the flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="518a1-112">Procedura obsługi dla <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized> zdarzenia używa kluczy do pobrania wartości semantyki utworzonych przy użyciu <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag.%23ctor%2A> z wyniku rozpoznawania.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-112">The handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized> event uses the keys to retrieve the semantics values created using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag.%23ctor%2A> from the recognition result.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
using System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
  
    // Initialize a SpeechRecognitionEngine object.  
    {  
      using (SpeechRecognitionEngine recognizer =  
         new SpeechRecognitionEngine(new System.Globalization.CultureInfo("en-US")))  
      {  
  
        // Build a rule with a list of cities, assign a semantic value to each city.  
        SrgsItem chi = new SrgsItem("Chicago");  
        chi.Add(new SrgsNameValueTag("ORD"));  
        SrgsItem bos = new SrgsItem("Boston");  
        bos.Add(new SrgsNameValueTag("BOS"));  
        SrgsItem mia = new SrgsItem("Miami");  
        mia.Add(new SrgsNameValueTag("MIA"));  
        SrgsItem dal = new SrgsItem("Dallas");  
        dal.Add(new SrgsNameValueTag("DFW"));  
  
        SrgsOneOf cities = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] { chi, bos, mia, dal });  
        SrgsRule citiesRule = new SrgsRule("flightCities");  
        citiesRule.Add(cities);  
  
        // Build the root rule, add rule references to the cities rule.  
        SrgsRule flightBooker = new SrgsRule("bookFlight");  
        flightBooker.Add(new SrgsItem("I want to fly from"));  
        flightBooker.Add(new SrgsRuleRef(citiesRule, "departureCity"));  
        flightBooker.Add(new SrgsItem("to"));  
        flightBooker.Add(new SrgsRuleRef(citiesRule, "arrivalCity"));  
  
        // Build an SrgsDocument object from the flightBooker rule and add the cities rule.  
        SrgsDocument cityChooser = new SrgsDocument(flightBooker);  
        cityChooser.Rules.Add(citiesRule);  
  
        // Create a Grammar object from the SrgsDocument and load it to the recognizer.  
        Grammar departArrive = new Grammar(cityChooser);  
        departArrive.Name = ("Cities Grammar");  
        recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(departArrive);  
  
        // Configure recognizer input.  
        recognizer.SetInputToDefaultAudioDevice();  
  
        // Attach a handler for the SpeechRecognized event.  
        recognizer.SpeechRecognized +=  
          new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
  
        // Start asynchronous recognition.  
        recognizer.RecognizeAsync();  
        Console.WriteLine("Starting asynchronous recognition...");  
  
        // Keep the console window open.  
        Console.ReadLine();  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Handle the SpeechRecognized event.  
    static void recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Speech recognized: " + e.Result.Text);  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Semantic results:");  
      Console.WriteLine("  The departure city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["departureCity"].Value);  
      Console.WriteLine("  The destination city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["arrivalCity"].Value);  
    }  
  }  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="518a1-117">Poniższy przykład tworzy gramatykę do wybierania miast dla lotu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-117">The following example creates a grammar for choosing the cities for a flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="518a1-118">W przykładzie zastosowano <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag.%23ctor%2A> przypisanie wartości semantycznej do każdego miasta, czyli kodu dla lotniska miasta.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="518a1-118">The example uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag.%23ctor%2A> to assign a semantic value to each city, which is the code for the city's airport.</span></span>  
  
